    "The susceptibility block is modified from the U-Net model (Ronneberger et al., 2015) with the backbone of Resent18 (He et al., 2015), where the model processes input information through the 18 blocks of Convolution, Batch Normalization (Ioffe and Szegedy, 2015b), dropout, Rectified Linear Unit (ReLU), and Max pooling (Wu and Gu, 2015) with a total 23 556 931 trainable parameters, which are variables that need to be optimized during the training process.",
    "The convolution layer in each block convolved with the 3 × 3 window, and it was initialized with the Glorot uniform initialization function (Glorot and Bengio, 2010)."
